<paragraph id="8F5E1A22FFBDFFA6FF413F54FEB9EE18" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1978]" box="[199,328,1832,1858]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F5E1A22FFBDFFA6FF413F2CFC5DEEE0" blockId="8.[151,1437,152,1978]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicName id="48E161A1FFBDFFA6FF413F2CFEBEEE33" box="[199,335,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Brontostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deferreri" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="BD95C630FFBDFFA6FF413F2CFEBEEE33" box="[199,335,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">B. deferreri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A6A67B4BFFBDFFA6FED33F2CFE41EE30" box="[341,432,1872,1898]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be separated from all the known species by its color pattern. It is the only species with three colors in the pronotum. The hemispherical tubercle on the ventro-posterior side of the head is unique in the genus, and the narrow connexivum is also distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C7FB49A9FFBCFFA5FF113EC3FB58EBE0" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="8F5E1A22FFBCFFA7FF113EC3FDA0EFA3" blockId="9.[151,1436,1727,1785]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
